            <title>[SPARK-11572] Exit AsynchronousListenerBus thread when stop() is called</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11572</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As vonnagy reported in the following thread:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://search-hadoop.com/m/q3RTtk982kvIow22&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://search-hadoop.com/m/q3RTtk982kvIow22&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attempts to join the thread in AsynchronousListenerBus resulted in lock up because AsynchronousListenerBus thread was still getting messages SparkListenerExecutorMetricsUpdate from the DAGScheduler&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposed fix is to check stopped flag within the loop of AsynchronousListenerBus thread&lt;/p&gt;</description>
